<TITLE> BTRC cuts inter-connectivity charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 24 (bdnews24.com)  BTRC has cut the inter-connectivity fee among the mobile phone and PSTN operators from Oct 1, the telecoms watchdog said in a statement Monday. The new inter-connectivity call charge will be 0.40 paisa a minute, down from 0.66 paisa, Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission has decided in a move to make calls cheaper. The telecoms regulator said the new decision had been made in consultative meetings with mobile phone and PSTN operators on Sept 16 and 20. bdn
